cs.CL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.FL, cs.PL

This paper deals with the formalism and parsing strategies of hybrid type-logical grammars, which are commonly used in computational linguistics and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the embedding of hybrid type-logical grammars into first-order linear logic, which falls under the category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also touches upon the problems with lambda grammars/abstract categorial grammars, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the syntax-semantics interface, which is related to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
